wdi-DT.TDS.DPPG.XP.ZS.def: Public and publicly guaranteed debt service is the sum of principal repayments and interest actually paid in currency, goods, or services on long-term obligations of public debtors and long-term private obligations guaranteed by a public entity. Exports refer to exports of goods, services, and income.
wdi-DT.TDS.DPPG.XP.ZS.name: Public and publicly guaranteed debt service
wdi-DT.TDS.DPPG.XP.ZS.dim: % of exports of goods, services and primary income
wdi-DT.TDS.DPPG.XP.ZS.units: % of exports of goods, services and primary income
